n code scenes in prompt-to-video.",[n.CustomCodeSceneRefinement]:"Enables visual QA refinement of custom code scenes after generation. Requires CustomCodeScenes.",[n.EnhancedEditorLibrary]:"Opts the workspace into the redesigned flow-editor Media Library (ARC-11125). Temporary while we roll out the new library.",[n.VoiceModelSelection]:"We want everyone to use v3 because it's superior, but even the same voice will sound differently than with v1 or v2 and some customers really want to keep it as it used to be.",[n.SuperscriptInTextEditor]:"Shows a superscript button in chapter step title/subtitle editors. Enable per workspace when a customer needs true superscript formatting (e.g. ® for Cotality/Encompass).",[n.PromptVideoWizard]:"Interactive prompt video: early editor + inspector wizard (clarifications, plan pick) then generation.",[n.Analytics30]:"Enables the Analytics 3.0 HubSpot CRM pull pipeline (deals/contacts/companies/pipelines → ClickHouse) and downstream ROI attribution. Flipping on triggers a backfill task. Customer must reconsent the HubSpot OAuth scopes (adds crm.objects.deals.read) for the pull to succeed.",[n.ManualStyleGuide]:'Internal-only iteration tool for the style-guide experiment. Reveals a "Style guide" textarea on the brand-kit settings page and a "Use manual style guide" checkbox on the video creation form. When the checkbox is ticked, the saved style guide substitutes the aesthetic + voice lines in the video-gen brand context (see ADR 0003). Workspace-only; never expose to customers by default.',[n.AllowLowConfidenceAudienceReveal]:"Re-includes low-confidence / fuzzy IP→company matches in Audience Reveal, leads export, the leads digest email, and HubSpot lead sync for this workspace. These weak vendor guesses are dropped globally by default (ARC-12570); enable per workspace only when a customer relied on the broader (less accurate) matching and explicitly accepts the reduced precision (ARC-12623)."},r.workspaceOnlyFeatures=[n.SuperscriptInTe